description:
{center:begin}{size: 35}About Ki Spheres{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_001.png} 
{size: 25}Collecting Ki Spheres increases 
a character's {color : #FF9900}Ki and ATK{color}, which results in 
more damage dealt to the enemy.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Ki Spheres{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_002.png} 
{size: 25}You can {color : #FF9900}collect multiple Ki Spheres 
of the same color{color} if they are 
next to one another.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Ki Spheres{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_003.png} 
{size: 25}If the collected Ki Spheres are the 
same color as the character's Type, 
you'll receive {color : #FF9900}double the amount of Ki{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Super Attacks{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_004.png} 
{size: 25}The character can perform a {color : #FF9900}Super Attack{color} 
if enough Ki has been accumulated.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Super Attacks{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_005.png} 
{size: 25}Super Attacks deal {color : #FF9900}great damage{color} 
to enemies. Some can also inflict 
{color : #FF9900}a variety of extra effects{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Type Match-Ups{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_009.png} 
{size: 25}If your character's {color : #FF9900}Type is advantageous 
against the enemy{color}, the character will 
be able to {color : #FF9900}guard and reduce damage 
taken from the enemy attack{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Type Match-Ups{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{center:begin}{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_008.png} 
{size: 25}In addition, if your character's Type is 
advantageous against the enemy, the 
{color : #FF9900}damage dealt to the enemy will increase{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Type Match-Ups{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{center:begin}{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_010.png} 
{size: 25}This time the enemy is an {color : #9900FF}INT Type{color} 
character, so {color : #FF9900}PHY Type{color} characters 
are advantageous against him.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Attack Order{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{center:begin}{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_006.png} 
{size: 25}The {color : #FF9900}enemy and ally icons at the 
bottom of the screen{color} represent the 
order in which characters will attack. 
Attacks will proceed from {color : #FF9900}left to right{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Attack Order{size}
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_007.png}{center}
{size: 25}For example, this battle will proceed as follows: 
1) Raditz will attack Goku 
2) Goku will attack Raditz 
3) Piccolo will attack Raditz{size}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Training{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_011.png} 
{size: 25}You can train characters to raise 
their level and {color : #FF9900}increase their stats{color}. 
Once characters have reached max level, 
you can {color : #CC33FF}Awaken{color} them to 
increase their strength further.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Training Locations{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{size: 25}By using a Training Location, you can 
train a character more effectively.{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_016.png} 
{size: 25}For example, using "King Kai's Planet (10G)" 
will result in the Training being a {color : #FF9900}Big Success{color}, 
which {color : #FF9900}grants an extra 20% EXP{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}Training Partners and 
Training Items{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_017.png} 
{size: 25}Undergoing Training consumes 
{color : #FF9900}Training Partners{color} and {color : #FF9900}Training Items{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}Training Partners{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_018.png} 
{size: 25}There is a chance of {color : #FF9900}leveling up 
a character's Super Attack{color} if you 
select a {color : #FF9900}character of the same name{color} 
as a Training Partner.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}Training Items{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_019.png} 
{size: 25}Using {color : #FF9900}Training Items of the same Type{color} 
as the character grants {color : #FF9900}an extra 50% EXP{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 25}Let's automatically select the 
Training Partners and Training Items this time. 

Tap the "Auto" buttons.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 25} Now, tap "Begin" to train.{size} 

{size:20}When Training commences, the chosen Training Partners, 
Training Items and Zeni will be consumed.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Awakening{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{size: 23}There are three types of Awakening: {color : #FF0000}Z-Awakening{color}, 
{color : #CC33FF}Dokkan Awakening{color} and {color : #FFCC00}Extreme Z-Awakening{color}. 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_012.png} 
Once a character has reached max level, 
you can awaken the character by 
consuming {color : #FF9900}Awakening Medals and Zeni{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Z-Awakening{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_013.png} 
{size: 25}Z-Awakening characters increases their stats. 

In addition, the {color : #FF9900}rarity will increase{color}, 
as will the {color : #FF9900}maximum level{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Z-Awakening{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_013.png} 
{size: 25}Z-Awakening will also add "Super" or 
"Extreme" to a character's Type. 
This will further {color : #FF9900}increase the character's 
attack power against the advantageous Type{color} 
as well as {color : #FF9900}increasing the character's resistance 
against the disadvantageous Type{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size:25}Now then, tap the "Z-Awaken" button.{size} 

{size:20}{color : #FF9900}The character's level will be raised to max level 
for the purpose of this tutorial{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Dokkan Awakening{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_014.png} 
{size:25}Certain characters can be {color : #CC33FF}Dokkan Awakened{color} 
after they have been Z-Awakened and 
reached max level. This Awakening 
requires {color : #FF9900}Awakening Medals and Zeni{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Dokkan Awakening{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_014.png} 
{size:25}Along with changes to the appearance, 
the character's {color : #FF9900}stats, Super Attack and 
skills will be powered up{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size:25}Tap the "Dokkan Awaken" button.{size} 

{size:18}Usually a character is reverted to Lv. 1 after Dokkan Awakening. 
However, {color : #FF9900}this time the character's level will be raised 
to max level for the purpose of this tutorial{color}.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 35}About Active Skills{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tut_common_dialog_title_line.png} 
{size: 25}A number of characters can launch {color : #FF9900}Active Skills{color} 
when certain conditions are met.{size} 
{initialImage: layout/image/tutorial/tutorial_ex_015.png} 
{size: 25}Active Skills can be activated in battle, and each 
has different activation conditions and effects.{size}{center}

{center:begin}{size: 25}Now that Goku has been Dokkan Awakened, 
he can use his Active Skill. 

{color : #FF9900}Swipe his character icon upwards{color} to use it.{size}{center}
